title: A Voyage round Great Britain; with short views of Aberdeen, Balmoral, ... Fécamp, Havre and Paris
author: Hargreaves, Thomas
snippet: In the same dock we found another Runcorn vessel, the ' Hilda,' just arrived, though six days longer out than ourselves. There was in the Victoria Dock a Government vessel with some officials on board. There are three docks in Aberdeen : the Victoria, the Albert, and the Upper Docks.
